@@TJvSpecialLabel
<TITLEIMG TJvSpecialLabel>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.LabelsAndStatic
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Displays a small animation for each letter.
Description
  Use TJvSpecialLabel to show a label that displays a small animation for each letter. Initially the
  label is empty, then the first letter changes until it is set to the correct letter; then the second
  letter changes, and so on, until the last letter from the caption is set, and the label text is 
  equal to the \string specified by Text. 
  
  Set property Text at runtime to start the animation. Use SleepTime to specify the interval between 
  animation events.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSpecialLabel.Create
Summary
  Creates and initializes a new TJvSpecialLabel object.
Description
  Use \Create to create and initialize a new TJvSpecialLabel object.
  
  \Create calls the inherited \Create method, then sets the initial values for the label as follows: 
  
  * SleepTime is set to 20.
  * Text is set to the \string specified in the Name property.
Parameters
  AOwner - A component, typically the form, that is responsible for freeing the label.
See Also
  SleepTime, Text
