@@TJvSpecialLabel.SleepTime
Summary
  Determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes between animation events.
Description
  SleepTime determines how frequently the animation event occurs. Each time the specified interval 
  passes, the last letter of the visible text is changed in the caption.

  Use SleepTime to specify any cardinal value as the interval between animation events. The default 
  value is 20 (1/50 second).
See Also
  Text
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSpecialLabel.Text
Summary
  Specifies the text \string that is used for the animation.
Description
  Use the Text property to read the text of the label or specify a new \string for the Text value. 
  By default, Text is the \string specified in the Name property.
  
  Set Text at runtime to start the animation
See Also
  SleepTime
